    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-12T11:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-12T11:36:00-05:00" n="671"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d671">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11988</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Admiral <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Florida. <lb/> Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-12T10:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1914, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mayo reports, April 11, 11 a.m.: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Received message from Zaragoza, substance being that he is ordered to
                            await instruction as to action in arrest matter. Have voluntarily
                            informed him that I will not report my failure to obtain promise of
                            reparation until noon April 12. Do not expect compliance with my demands
                            and consider it desirable that Department’s instructions as to further
                            procedure reach me promptly.</p>
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayo</hi>.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head"
                        >[Untitled]</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-12T23:30:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1914, 11.30 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>I have received from Embassy, dated Sunday afternoon, April 12, the
                        following: <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>Positive refusal of Mexican Government, in writing, to accede to
                                demand of Admiral Mayo relative to the salute at Tampico.</p>
                        </quote>
                    </p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                        </signed>.</closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
